parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS Hydraulic Control Unit (HCU) can cause the loss of brakes, either front, rear, or both, leading to a significant reduction in stopping ability and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes hard or stuck
the brake lever is impossible to squeeze
the ABS system fails without warning

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake fluid can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to the loss of brakes, either front, rear, or both, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake fluid needs to be changed every two years
the ABS system fails without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TBW connector can cause the motorcycle to lose throttle and go into limp mode, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: the check engine light comes on
the motorcycle goes into limp mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the compensator sprocket on starters can cause the starter to not engage fully, leading to difficulties in starting the motorcycle and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The starter does not engage fully
the motorcycle is difficult to start.

the motorcycle goes into limp mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETC system can cause the motorcycle to lose throttle and go into limp mode, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
